rComments: His enthusiasm makes what could easily be an awful class really interesting and fun.  The class is hard and you really can't miss a lecture, but he's happy to answer questions and great at clarifying when necessary.
Obviously cares about making it good. Can be a little tough to understand his explanations, but just ask to clarify.

HARD course, so work hard in return.  As for Youri, he is genuine and passionate about Semantics.  He is extremely helpful, goes his way to offer aid to his students, and does all he can to make sure you get the material.  Fair + understanding.  Funny + interesting.  Good guy all around.  I'm not intimidated to go to his office hours at all.
Unless you're an A student, stay away!
